name: computer hell
description:
Using the pattern called “computer sound“ in the section “funny” of the CASIO SA-35, I generated some random sounds by adding a fuzz, two delays, a reverb and a synthwah/envelope filter pedals together. Therefore,  I intended to create variations with the rhythm while also experiencing with textures as I manipulated the pedals. 
Recorded with an old Casio toy and some effects , using an old brazilian Giannini Baguinho amplifier and captured with a sm57 microphone.

First piece of the collection “casio weirdo”, unusual music and noise experiments in an old Casio toy keyboard.
